Edward Tracey (born 5 June 1943) is an Irish boxer. He competed in the men's featherweight event at the 1968 Summer Olympics. At the 1968 Summer Olympics, he defeated Errol West of Jamaica, before losing to Antonio Rold√°n of Mexico.
